image.altText: A police officer has his back to the camera as he walks towards some police tape.

props.synopsis: Ronald Martin and Jeremy Scrutton pleaded guilty to fatally stabbing the man with a "butcher-style knife", during an attack at an Alice Springs home in June 2020.

title.children: Pair plead guilty to manslaughter over fatal stabbing of Jacinta Nampijinpa Price's nephew

image.altText: Russell Brand leaves the Troubabour Wembley Park theatre. He is wearing sunglasses at night.

props.synopsis: A woman who accused British actor and comedian Russell Brand of sexual and emotional abuse says his denial of the allegations is "insulting".

title.children: 'Laughable and insulting': Russell Brand accuser hits out at his denials in fresh interview

image.altText: A car parked next to a football pitch. Police tape is stretched across part of the area. Several police are on the pitch.

props.synopsis: ACT police confirm two 20-year-old female students are in hospital after a stabbing at the Australian National University in Canberra.

title.children: Two students in hospital after stabbing at Australian National University

image.altText: A composite image of a Triton unmanned surveillance aircraft and a P-8 Poseidon

props.synopsis: Australia will upgrade its fleet of P-8 patrol aircraft so they can eventually fire missiles out to 1,000 kilometres, while also purchasing another long-range Triton drone from the United States.

title.children: P-8A Poseidon upgrade and fourth Triton drone part of $1.5b boost to RAAF

image.altText: A woman with long brown hair in a white blazer standing in front of a Vote No poster.

props.synopsis: Leading critics of the Indigenous Voice to Parliament have gathered in Adelaide for one of the biggest No campaign events so far, with one accusing supporters of the proposal of resorting to "bullying" and "gaslighting".

title.children: Leading Voice opponent uses Adelaide gathering to hit out at Yes supporters

image.altText: Lyn Read is sitting, wearing an aqua green jumper. With her dog between her arms.

props.synopsis: It was a highly sophisticated yet common scam. One that cost Lyn Read $50,000. Money the terminal cancer patient was saving for her last days and to pay for her funeral.

title.children: Lyn Read lost $50,000 in a scam, money she needs to pay for her funeral

image.altText: A Chinese air force pilot flies a military jet in full uniform and helmet.

props.synopsis: Taiwan tells China to stop its "destructive unilateral actions" after more than 100 Chinese warplanes and nine navy ships are detected in areas around the self-ruled island.

title.children: 'High alert': Taiwan detects 103 Chinese warplanes around island

image.altText: Missing woman Tina Greer smiles as she gives a 'peace' sign with her hand in a park.

props.synopsis: There is "no doubt" a Gold Coast woman was murdered by her now dead bikie boyfriend in 2012, an inquest has heard.

title.children: The day Tina Greer went missing her bikie boyfriend's car was suspiciously clean, inquest told

image.altText: People running across a dirt road in a remote community in front of a house

props.synopsis: Long-standing tensions between feuding family groups reached crisis point in the Northern Territory's remote west in early 2022. The response of two police officers has now been recognised.

title.children: 'A very intense situation': NT police officers win bravery award for Wadeye riot response

props.synopsis: A fire being treated as suspicious destroys 40 cars and two trailers at an automotive business at South Kempsey on the NSW Mid North Coast.

title.children: Family automotive business devastated after suspicious fire destroys 40 cars

image.altText: Courtroom panel, headed by a sign that says Ukraine

props.synopsis: A Russian representative has told the UN's highest court that Ukraine's claims Russia abused the UN Genocide Convention to start a war between the two nations were "hopelessly flawed".

title.children: 'Hopelessly flawed': Russia launches legal attack on Ukraine in UN's top court

image.altText: A close up photo of a phone with dating apps like Tinder, Grindr and Bumble on the screen.

props.synopsis: Popular online dating platforms are being threatened with greater government regulation unless they lift their standards and improve safety for users.

title.children: Dating apps threatened with regulation unless they improve safety

image.altText: A man arriving at a courthouse before a sentencing hearing.

props.synopsis: A court hears 60-year-old Raymond John O'Brien, a disgruntled tenant, walked into the Kalgoorlie agency last December and told a woman behind the front counter to leave, saying "I'm going to burn this place down".

title.children: Man who torched outback real estate agency, doused woman in petrol has 'paranoid personality', court hears

image.altText: A keyboard lights up in darkness

props.synopsis: A 31-year-old man is charged over a series of alleged online offences committed against children over a five-year period, following a "significant investigation" involving Tasmanian and federal police.

title.children: Joint operation arrests man over 98 alleged offences against children over five-year period

image.altText: Prisoners released during a prisoner swap deal between US and Iran, arrive at Doha International Airport.

props.synopsis: Five US citizens have left Iran and landed in Doha in a prisoner swap for five Iranians held in the United States, and the transfer of $US6 billion in frozen Iranian assets.

title.children: US prisoners 'finally coming home' in rare prisoner swap with Iran

image.altText: AFL legend Ron Barassi stands smiling on the MCG wearing a Melbourne AFL scarf.

props.synopsis: The AFL Commission will make a final decision as calls grow for the league to rename the premiership cup after Australian sporting icon Ron Barassi, as the Victorian government confirms a state memorial to honour his life and work.

title.children: AFL weighs up naming premiership cup in honour of Ron Barassi

image.altText: A man holds a bike and a pair of sunglasses

props.synopsis: A cyclist who temporarily lost his sight after a magpie attack in northern Victoria is urging others to better protect themselves.

title.children: Surgeon rebuilds cyclist's eye after swooping magpie causes severe damage

image.altText: A man in a suit walks past news cameras as he stares straight ahead

props.synopsis: Danushka Gunathilaka, 32, pleads not guilty to one count of sexual intercourse without consent after he went back to the woman's eastern Sydney home in November last year.

title.children: 'I felt fearful for my life': Court hears Sri Lankan cricketer was allegedly forceful, choked woman during sex

image.altText: The face of a happy boy

props.synopsis: Dawlon Smith-Saunders was riding a scooter outside a supermarket in Bli Bli at on September 3 when he was hit by a ute and suffered severe head and limb injuries.

title.children: Family makes heartbreaking decision to switch off life support for 12yo boy hit by ute

image.altText: Tameka Yallop (blurry in the foreground) carries her daughter as she waves to an applauding crowd at the FIFA Women's World Cup.

props.synopsis: The Matildas will move an Olympic qualifier to Perth Stadium to accommodate tens of thousands more fans trying to get tickets.

title.children: Extra 40,000 tickets to be made available for Matildas' Olympic qualifier after move to bigger stadium

image.altText: Woman stands in a carpark wearing a shirt saying "history is calling".

props.synopsis: A woman was refused entry to an AFLW game after a security guard told her she couldn't wear a "political shirt" into the venue.

title.children: Woman refused access to AFLW match for wearing 'Yes' shirt

image.altText: Chris Bowen in a navy suit and tie in  front of the australian flag at a press conference

props.synopsis: The federal government releases figures to try to shut down growing calls from the opposition to consider nuclear as part of Australia's future energy mix, with Energy Minister Chris Bowen saying there would be a "massive cost to pay".

title.children: Energy Minister says replacing coal-fired power stations with nuclear would cost $387 billion

image.altText: Five men wearing PPE gear and face masks look on as they stand amongst rubble and debris

props.synopsis: People whose homes were swept away by flooding in Libya's eastern city of Derna a week ago are facing the dilemma of whether to stay and risk infection or flee through areas where landmines have been displaced by the torrents.

title.children: Libyan flood survivors weigh water shortages against landmine risk

image.altText: Students in a classroom with male teacher in background.

props.synopsis: Poor mental health and excessive screen time are the biggest problems facing young people, according to a new survey of more than 2,000 Australian teachers. New resources will be made available for teachers in a hope to create more conversations on mental wellbeing.

title.children: 'Nervous rants' and crying at school: Teachers say poor mental health is the biggest issue facing Australia's youth

image.altText: Paul has dark hair and a beard and wears a blue jacket with white flowers on his lapel and a patterned bowtie.

props.synopsis: The family of Paul Grapsas has issued a statement, describing him as a man of integrity who was expecting his third child.

title.children: Geelong man whose body was found after nightly dog walk was expecting his third child, family reveals

image.altText: White and yellow drone in the sky

props.synopsis: Global drone delivery company Wing is shifting to be based out of shopping centres for easier access to deliverable goods and says so far it hasn't been able to find a suitable shopping centre in Canberra.

title.children: Drone service Wing stops delivering food in Canberra

image.altText: A firefighter dousing a massive blaze in water, smoke, trees burning.

props.synopsis: Longer and complex fire seasons are placing increased pressure on rural fire brigades but a shortage of volunteers has raised concerns only a handful will be shouldering the load.

title.children: Fears lives could be lost due to lack of volunteer rural firefighters during 'traumatic fire season'

image.altText: Eddie JOnes looks past a Wallabies player

props.synopsis: Wallabies coach Eddie Jones apologises for their loss to Fiji in the group stage at the Rugby World Cup, which has them in danger of not making the quarterfinals for the first time.

title.children: 'They should be throwing croissants at me': Eddie Jones takes full responsibility for Wallabies' historic loss

image.altText: A long-haired man in a black wetsuit stands on the sand, holding a long yellow surfboard with a snake on the front of it.

props.synopsis: Authorities say the man had a permit to keep native animals, but did not have a permit to take the reptile out in public.

title.children: Pet python surfing session costs owner thousands after wildlife officers chase up viral footage

image.altText: A small parchment book with Arabic script

props.synopsis: Khaled Sabsabi was looking for exceptional stories in Muslim families' homes when he found a manuscript collection bigger than any owned by museums.

title.children: 'Mind-blowing' collections uncovered as artist looks to the suburbs for untold stories
